    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "test: Improve loopback address check in `rpc_bind.py`",
    "user": {
      "login": "xyzconstant",
      "id": 263061129,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOD63-iQ",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/263061129?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/xyzconstant",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xyzconstant/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "A [loopback address](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/computer-networks/what-is-a-loopback-address/) can range from `127.0.0.0` to `127.255.255.255`. This commit relaxes the loopback check in `rpc_bind.py` by checking whether an IP address (from `all_interfaces()`) starts with `'127.'` instead of strictly matching `'127.0.0.1'`.\r\n\r\nPrograms like VPNs might add an extra loopback address (e.g., 127.1.130.83), which failed under the previous state. These addresses will now pass with this update.\r\n\r\n---\r\n**For context:** I found this while running tests with the Mullvad daemon active. Mullvad adds a custom lo0 interface like `inet 127.141.11.239 netmask 0xff000000` that failed with `--nonloopback`, which should not be the case since the address is a valid loopback IP.",
